President Uhuru Kenyatta and DP William Ruto are not leaving anything to chance in their reelection bid as the PSs and CSs are seen to be campaigning forthem. With only six months left to the poll, the opposition has been accusing Jubilee of using state officers and machine to campaign for them.Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho has on several occasions accused Coast regional coordinator Nelson Marwa of being &ldquo;a politician in uniform.&rdquo; CSs Najib Balala (Tourism) and Charles Keter (Energy) have in their speeches been viewed as campaigning for Jubilee.Interior CS Joseph Nkaissery has also been accused by the opposition of engaging in politics. On Tuesday in Mombasa, Gender Affairs PS Zeinab Hussein urged women to vote for Uhuru and Ruto.